Interface LongToFloatFunction1

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Arity, FunctionN<java.lang.Float>, InputChainable<java.lang.Long>, InputChainableInput<java.lang.Long>, ResultChainable<java.lang.Float>, ResultChainableResult<java.lang.Float>, ToFloatFunctionN, Unboxed<Function1<java.lang.Long,java.lang.Float>>, UnboxedAll<Function1<java.lang.Long,java.lang.Float>,ToFloatFunction1<java.lang.Long>,LongFunction1<java.lang.Float>>, UnboxedInput<ToFloatFunction1<java.lang.Long>>, UnboxedResult<LongFunction1<java.lang.Float>>
    Functional Interface:
    This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.

    @FunctionalInterface
public interface LongToFloatFunction1
extends ToFloatFunctionN, InputChainableInput<java.lang.Long>, UnboxedAll<Function1<java.lang.Long,java.lang.Float>,ToFloatFunction1<java.lang.Long>,LongFunction1<java.lang.Float>>
    Represents a function that accepts a long-valued argument and produces a float-valued result. This is the one-arity specialization of ToFloatFunctionN. This is the long-consuming primitive specialization of ToFloatFunction1. This is the float-producing primitive specialization of LongFunction1.

    This is a functional interface whose functional method is applyAsFloat(long).

    Since:
    3.0.0
